## STEP 4A — Per-Holding Analysis & Action Ratings

---

### A17U — CapitaLand Ascendas REIT | **ADD**

**Current:** SGD 2.57 | Forward yield: ~5.93% | Mkt value: SGD 11,462 | Next earnings: 5 May 2026

The 1Q FY2026 business update (27 Apr) showed portfolio occupancy dipping for the third consecutive quarter to 90.5% (from 91.8% in 2Q FY2025), reflecting a softening in some markets. However, this is offset by robust rental reversions of **+10.6%** for the quarter — a double-digit positive reversion signals landlord pricing power and suggests income quality holds up even as occupancy ebbs. Gross revenue and NPI grew low single-digits in FY2025, and distributable income rose 1.4%. The REIT's diversification across Singapore, Australia, the UK/Europe, and the US industrial/logistics sector provides geographic resilience. At SGD 2.57 with a near-6% forward yield and upcoming 1H FY2026 distribution (ex-div was 31 March, payment 30 April), this is a **core income anchor** of the SGX portfolio. ADD on dips below SGD 2.50 to build position toward a target of 6,000–7,000 units.

---

### C52 — ComfortDelGro | **ADD**

**Current:** SGD 1.48 | Yield: ~5.7–6.1% | Mkt value: SGD 4,440 | Ex-div: 4 May 2026

ComfortDelGro is approaching its May 4 ex-dividend date with a cash dividend of SGD 0.046. The full-year FY2026 consensus DPS is SGD 0.09, which is an increase from the trailing SGD 0.085 — a positive signal on dividend trajectory. Analyst consensus target of SGD 1.633 represents **10.4% upside** from current levels. The company is recovering its international operations (UK, Australia) and domestic taxi/bus margins are stabilizing post-pandemic. The only near-term news of note is a board reshuffle following the passing of Independent Director Prof Ooi Beng Chin on 25 April — governance continuity, but no material operational impact. The combination of a high single-digit yield, double-digit price upside, and incoming dividend makes this an **attractive ADD** ahead of the ex-date. Consider building toward 5,000 units for a more meaningful income contribution.

